@startuml parallel-mergesort-game-flow
!theme plain
!include ../shared/theme.puml
skinparam ActivityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #F0F8FF
skinparam PartitionBackgroundColor #FAFAFA

title Performing Parallel Merge Sort with the Existing Tool

|#LightBlue| System |
|#LightGreen| All Players |
|#LightYellow| Merger (Main Thread) |
|#LightPink| Non-Merger (Blocked) |

|System|
start
:Generate **n** shuffled cards\nin shared container;
:Divide cards into **p** equal\npartitions (one per player);
note right
  Partition dividers appear
  in the shared container.
  Each zone highlighted
  in a player's color.
end note
:Assign each partition\nto a player;

|All Players|
partition "**Phase 1 — Local Sort** (parallel, independent)" {
    fork
        :Player 1 sorts\npartition 1\nusing private buffer;
    fork again
        :Player 2 sorts\npartition 2\nusing private buffer;
    fork again
        :Player **p** sorts\npartition **p**\nusing private buffer;
    end fork
    note right
      Each player works **only**
      on their assigned zone.
      Buffer contiguity check
      enforces coherent subsets.
      ——
      **Maps to:** embarrassingly
      parallel local computation
    end note
    :Each player clicks\n"Local Sort Done";
}

|System|
:All local sorts validated;\n→ **Barrier activates**;
note right
  Reuses existing
  **BarrierManager** FSM:
  RUNNING → WAITING
  → BARRIER_ACTIVE
end note

partition "**Phase 2 — Merge Rounds** (⌈log₂ p⌉ rounds)" {
    repeat
        :Pair adjacent players\nfor this merge round;
        note right
          Round **k**: merge
          2^(k-1)-size sorted runs
          into 2^k-size runs
        end note

        fork
            |Merger (Main Thread)|
            :Merge two adjacent\nsorted runs into one;
            note right
              Merger interacts with
              shared container.
              Other player's cards
              become visible.
              ——
              **Maps to:** reduction /
              tree-based merging
            end note
        fork again
            |Non-Merger (Blocked)|
            :See lock overlay\n(barrier active);
            note right
              **Maps to:** thread
              idle time / sync cost
            end note
        end fork

        |System|
        :Validate merged run\nis sorted;
        :Release barrier\n→ next round;
    repeat while (More merge rounds?) is (yes)
    -> no;
}

|System|
:All cards in ascending order\n→ **Game complete!**;
note right
  Single fully sorted array
  in shared container.
  Show completion stats:
  time, moves, rounds.
end note
stop

center footer Players perform Parallel Merge Sort using existing shared container, buffers, and barriers

@enduml
